This is Perl module Net::DNS::Hosts.

INSTALLATION

Type the following command:

    $ curl -L http://cpanmin.us | perl - Net::DNS::Hosts

Or install cpanm and then run the following command to install
Net::DNS::Hosts:

    $ cpanm Net::DNS::Hosts

If you get an archive of this distribution, unpack it and build it
as per the usual:

    $ tar xzf Net-DNS-Hosts-$version.tar.gz
    $ cd Net-DNS-Hosts-$version
    $ perl Makefile.PL
    $ make && make test

Then install it:

    $ make install

DOCUMENTATION

Net::DNS::Hosts documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    $ perldoc Net::DNS::Hosts

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

